    <header>
      <h1>Process</h1>
      <p>I design content systems and workflows that allow teams to deliver high-quality content efficiently, using automation and tooling to reduce friction while maintaining strong quality controls.</p>
    </header>

    <div class="project-section" id="dark-web-monitoring">
      <div class="project-header">
        <h2>AI-based translation app</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="project-content">
        <p><strong>Problem</strong>: Localizing a website is costly, time-consuming, and potentially error-prone.</p>
        <p><strong>Solution</strong>: I designed and implemented an LLM-powered app that integrates with content management systems and provides inexpensive, instantaneous, and high-quality translations.</p>

        <div class="more-content">
          <p><strong>Impact</strong>:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Reduced translation costs by over 99% and turnaround time from days or weeks to minutes.</li>
            <li>Gave our team more oversight of translation quality and eliminated gaps in translated content due to process problems.</li>
            <li>Enabled product, marketing, and CX teams to reuse the workflow across multiple content surfaces.</li>
          </ul>

          <p><strong>Details</strong>: Modern LLMs are excellent translators, especially for simple, concrete writing such as you find in good support content.</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Integration with Zendesk and any major LLM.</li>
            <li>Bulk translation of multiple articles at once.</li>
            <li>Targeted translation of individual articles and preview before publishing.</li>
            <li>Full or partial translation based on changed sections.</li>
            <li>Ad hoc translation of shorter texts.</li>
            <li>Integration with an in-house glossary.</li>
          </ul>

          <img src="static/images/translation-queue.png" alt="Translation queue" class="project-image">
          <img src="static/images/translation-individual.png" alt="Individual translation" class="project-image">
        </div>

        <p class="read-more">See details</p>
      </div>
    </div>

